This is the SST Model Creation Tool it will assist your in developing
models for the SST Simulation Framework. This tool assumes
that SST 7.1 or greater has been installed and is running on
your system. 

As part of the model development process you will be asked edit
files. The tool tool will use your EDITOR environment
variable as the preferred editor if it is set. If the EDITOR
environment variable is not set gedit is used by default.
The editors will be brought up when necessary in the model
development process. Tool allows you to exit and edit off-line
if you prefer and re-enter the process at point where you 
left off.

The tool is set up basically in three different phases.

   1) Model Creation from a template (Model Creator tab)
   2) Connecting Multiple models togeter that communicate (Model Connector tab)
   3) Converting models to templates (Model2Template button)

Tool tips are available if you mouse over each button
More specific Help is also availble by selecting the correct option
under the Help button.

About -> This file
Model Creator -> Model Creator tab functionality
Model Connector -> Model Connector tab functionality
Model to Template Convertor -> Model2Template button functionality

When appropriate information for each step is displayed in the 
Information screen.


